[ProMED-mail thanks Mahmoud Orabi for submitting this report.

Australia has several mosquito-borne viruses. Vector mosquito populations, and hence virus transmission, is dependent on rainfall to provide breeding habitat. The above report indicates that current La Ni√±a conditions have increased rainfall and some flooding providing breeding sites for _Culex annulirostris__ mosquitoes. The appearance of JE virus on mainland Australia illustrates the changes in virus distribution and spread into new areas that can occur and the importance of ongoing surveillance.

